info.author: Lucas Mendes Tortelli
info.description:
This package provides statistical indicators for Maximum Accuracy Interval
Arithmetic.
The Interval Arithmetic is a mathematical tool for the solution of problems
related to numerical errors, based on an algebraic system formed by all closed
intervals of Real Line.
The Interval Statistical Indicators are quantitative metrics for analyse population and amostral datasets. When used with Interval Arithmetic provide a high accuracy and confiability.
For more information about this study, see related works:
